crop to Wales outline

uk_outline <- raster::getData('GADM', country='GBR', level=1)

wales_outline <- uk_outline[uk_outline$NAME_1 == "Wales",]

wales_outline <- spTransform(wales_outline, crs(newproj))

wales_cropped <- crop(wales_osgb, wales_outline)

plot(wales_cropped)

# calculates the altitudinal differences between cells
altDiff <- function(x){x[2] - x[1]}

# Number of neighbour cells to use in LCP calculation 
directions <- 16

hd <- transition(wales_cropped, altDiff, directions, symm=FALSE)
## Warning in .TfromR(x, transitionFunction, directions, symm): transition
## function gives negative values
slope <- geoCorrection(hd)

adj <- adjacent(wales_cropped, cells=1:ncell(wales_cropped), pairs=TRUE, directions)

cost <- slope

cost[adj] <- 6 * exp(-3.5 * abs(slope[adj] + 0.05))

Conductance <- geoCorrection(cost)

Conductance is…

plot(raster(Conductance))

roman_roads <- readOGR("roman_roads.shp")
## OGR data source with driver: ESRI Shapefile 
## Source: "roman_roads.shp", layer: "roman_roads"
## with 392 features
## It has 11 fields
roman_roads <- spTransform(roman_roads, crs(newproj))

plot(roman_roads, col = "red")

roads_in_wales <- gContainsProperly(wales_outline, roman_roads, byid = TRUE)

wales_roads <- roman_roads[as.vector(roads_in_wales),]

plot(wales_cropped)
plot(wales_roads, col = "red", add = TRUE)

LCP_roads_dist <- data.frame()

for (i in unique(wales_roads$Name)) {
  known_pts <- gInterpolate(wales_roads[wales_roads$Name == i,], d = seq(0, gLength(wales_roads[wales_roads$Name == i,]), by = gLength(wales_roads[wales_roads$Name == i,])), normalized = FALSE)
  known_pts@coords
  A <- known_pts@coords[1,]
  B <- known_pts@coords[2,]
  AtoB <- shortestPath(Conductance, A, B, output="SpatialLines")
  LCP_pts <- gInterpolate(AtoB, d = seq(0, gLength(AtoB), by = 250), normalized = FALSE)  
  dist <- as.data.frame(t(gDistance(LCP_pts, wales_roads[wales_roads$Name == i,], byid = TRUE)))
  colnames(dist) <- "Distance"
  AtoBdf <- SpatialPointsDataFrame(LCP_pts, data.frame(distance = dist[,1]), match.ID = FALSE)
  wgs_road_pts <- spTransform(AtoBdf, "+init=epsg:4326")
  pt_coord <- as.data.frame(coordinates(wgs_road_pts))
  pt_coord_dist <- cbind(pt_coord, dist)
  pt_coord_dist$road_name <- i
  LCP_roads_dist <- rbind(LCP_roads_dist, pt_coord_dist)
}
